title: A controversial part of Robinhood's business tripled in sales thanks to high-frequency trading firms
text: Order routing revenue at Robinhood surged in 2018, according to new data.

title: Deutsche And Other Scandal-Plagued Banks Should Learn From Novartis, Tenneco, And Volkswagen
text: When Novartis, Tenneco, and Volkswagen chief compliance officers share advice publicly about reforming corporate culture, bank executives would do well to pay close attention.

title: Expectations for first-quarter growth have suddenly surged past 2%
text: First quarter growth perked up late in the quarter, to well above 2% after looking to be 1% or less when the economy was being hit by winter storms and the government shutdown.

title: Uber To Sell Minority Stake Of Its Autonomous Vehicle Unit To Japanese Consortium
text: Uber Technologies is planning to sell a 14 percent stake in its autonomous vehicle unit to existing investor Softbank, Japanese automaker Toyota, and auto parts manufacturer Denso ahead of its much-anticipated initial public offering (IPO), which is expected to happen in May.

title: Hookipa Pharma shares off to lackluster start in trading debut
text: Hookipa Pharma Inc. shares  were barely changed in their trading debut on Thursday, after the biotech priced its initial public offering at the low end of its price range.

title: Chinese electric sports car Qiantu K50 by Mullen coming to US roads next year
text: The K50 sits low and wide, with classic supercar proportions, and the partners behind the project are betting there is an emerging and still largely untapped market for high-performance electric cars.

title: As Earnings Season Rolls On Market Gets Mixed Economic Data From Europe, US
text: On the last trading day of the week, investors were greeted with some mixed economic data as earnings season is turning out to be better than expected.

title: StockTwits To Launch Commission-Free Trading App
text: StockTwits is launching commission-free stock trading starting in the second quarter.

title: SLANG, Compass Cannabis Execs Talk Industry Development: 'Capital Flows To ... Where It's Most Rewarded'
text: The two discussed the intersection of Canada's newly legalized industry with the burgeoning U.S. market.

title: US retail sales soared 1.6% in March
text: U.S. retail sales were expected to rise 0.9% in March, after slipping 0.2% a month earlier.

title: Why Isn't Big Pharma More Active In Cannabis?
text: The cannabis space has seen a few large-scale deals in the medical space, but this begs the question: why isn't big pharma much more involved in the industry?

title: Keyboards will be gone in five years and voice tech is 'the opportunity of a decade,' investor says
text: Voice-enabled tech will end the need for keyboards within five years, a venture capitalist with a track record for successful bets says.

title: Phantom Auto closes Series A funding, expands plans for remote-controlled autonomous vehicles
text: Phantom Auto, a start-up firm in Mountain View, said it raised approximately $19 million in Series A financing led by venture capital firm, Bessemer Venture Partners.

title: China's auto sales slide may be obscuring a demand shift in the industry's largest market
text: New energy vehicle sales in China have been growing, while the overall auto industry has seen sales decline.
